                        <div id="starterKit_2" class="hidden">
                            <div class="col s12 m9 l10">
                                <div id="whatIdeaLabExpects" class="row scrollspy">
                                    <h3>What do we expect from our <span class="idea-word">Idea</span><span class="lab-word">Lab</span> fellows?</h3>
                                    <p class="flow-text">Upon their graduation from the IdeaLab program, we hope to populate the Carolinian community with Carolinians with an authentic Warrior Spirit. We hope to fill student organizations, Student Councils, and political parties with open-minded servant leaders who put service above politics, service above positions, and service above recognitions. 
                You being here right now is not an accident. You have responded to the call for change. Now, it is time to change what you are called to do!</p>
                                </div>
                                <div id="fellowshipStarterKit" class="row scrollspy">
                                    <h3 class="center-align">The Fellowship Starter Kit</h3>
                                    <p class="flow-text">So, let’s get started with a few things that we would like to know about you! The following exercises will help you get to know more about yourself as a person. Why you are here at this very point of your life and why you decided to become a student leader are among the things these exercises will try to elicit from you.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div id="verbTest" class="scrollspy">
                                    <h4>The Verb Test</h4>
                                    <img src="assets/img/verb_test.jpg" width="225px" class="responsive-img" align="left"/><p class="flow-text">In class, we are often asked to describe ourselves: happy, inquisitive, the class clown, or everyone’s princess. But how do you describe yourself as a verb? In this activity, write down three action verbs that best describes yourself. Reflect deeply on your experiences on the things that you have constantly done so far in your life.</p>
                                    <p class="flow-text">Write these verbs down in a journal or notebook and briefly explain why they best describe you. This will be shared during the plenary session on Saturday.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div id="leadershipStory" class="scrollspy">
                                    <h4>Your Leadership Story</h4>
                                    <img src="assets/img/your_leadership_story.jpg" width="225px" class="responsive-img" align="right"><p class="flow-text">Marc Ong’s call for a Colorless SSC called for a break from the traditional way of student politics in USC. He called for student leadership that goes beyond party colors. His story was your story—a story about change, about hope, about being inspired to redefine the scope of Carolinian student leadership and to redesign a clearly flawed system in student governance.</p>
                                    <p class="flow-text">In this exercise, we would like you to dig deep into your holistic experience as a person. Try to go back as far into your childhood, replay those experiences and try to put together the dots. Try to build those experiences until it has converged to where you are now, reading this kit and thinking about your leadership story.</p>
                                    <p class="flow-text">What we would like you to do is to build a nonlinear timeline of your leadership story (see the example below). Why chart your leadership story in a nonlinear way? It’s because how things fall in place isn’t exactly straightforward. For example, some experiences way back in the past that may not have been connected with a series of events may actually be influencing your decisions now.</p>
                                    <img src="assets/img/timeline.png" class="responsive-img" style="display: block; margin: 0 auto"/>
                                    <p class="flow-text center-align">A nonlinear timeline</p>
                                </div>
                                <div id="whyHowWhat" class="row scrollspy">
                                    <h3>Why, How, and What</h3>
                                    <p class="flow-text">Watch the following TED Talk video by Simon Sinek, <em>Start with Why – How Great Leaders Inspire Action</em></p>
                                    <div class="video-container">
                                        <iframe width="420" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/u4ZoJKF_VuA" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="flow-text">Ask yourself the following questions:
                                        <blockquote style="border-left: 5px solid #92d050;">
                                            <ol class="flow-text">
                                                <li>Why are you here with this group? Why did you become a student leader in USC?</li>
                                                <li>How do you do things as a student leader? How do you translate your passion into concrete action?</li>
                                                <li>What do you plan to contribute to the Carolinian community? What project or advocacy do you plan to offer the Carolinian community?</li>
                                            </ol>
                                        </blockquote>
                                    </p>
                                    <div class="col s12 m9">
                                        <p class="flow-text">Write down your answers in a notebook or journal using the Golden Circle Framework. When you try answering these questions, reflect on your student leadership story and the verb you have chosen to describe yourself. Think of what you have done why you have gotten to where you are right now. Ask yourself again why you chose your verb and how does it reflect on your personal brand of leadership.</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col s12 m3">
                                        <img src="assets/img/golden_circle_framework.png" class="responsive-img"/>
                                        <p class="center-align">The Golden Circle Framework of Innovation</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div id="strengthsTest" class="row scrollspy">
                                    <h3>The Strengths Test</h3>
                                    <p class="flow-text">To take the VIA Survey of Character Strengths, you have to register into the <a href="https://www.authentichappiness.sas.upenn.edu/user/register">Authentic Happiness Website</a> and fill in the information you need to indicate. You will receive a confirmation message in your email address. Once confirmed, go to the <a href="https://www.authentichappiness.sas.upenn.edu/testcenter">Authentic Happiness Test Center</a> website, go to the “Engagement Questionnaires” section, and click “Take Test” for the VIA Survey of Character Strengths. The VIA Survey is a comprehensive test containing 240 questions that will gauge a general view of your character strengths.</p>
                                    <p class="flow-text">Once you have accomplished answering the Survey, please send us a copy of your results. You may forward your results to Kuya Luigi Kho through his email address.</p>
                                    <p class="flow-text">We look forward to knowing about your stories! And we hope you’ll join us in our fight to redefine student leadership in USC! </p>
                                </div> 
